

'''P2P Algorithms''' = "'''algorithms for fully distributed, totally serverless, fully scalable, globally searchable, robust, efficient peer-to-peer systems'''. These algorithms make it possible to make millions or even billions of computers work together in an organised manner without any central servers, without any computer being a boss over the others."
(http://events.ccc.de/congress/2005/fahrplan/events/461.en.html)

For more information, see David Göthberg's page, at http://www.pjort.com/projects/

